ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.144                Enzyme
NAME        geranyllinalool synthase;
            TPS04/GES;
            GES
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     geranylgeranyl diphosphate diphosphate-lyase ((E,E)-geranyllinalool-forming)
REACTION    geranylgeranyl diphosphate + H2O = (E,E)-geranyllinalool + diphosphate [RN:R10533]
ALL_REAC    R10533
SUBSTRATE   geranylgeranyl diphosphate [CPD:C00353];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     (E,E)-geranyllinalool [CPD:C20681];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     The enzyme is a component of the herbivore-induced indirect defense system. The product, (E,E)-geranyllinalool, is a precursor to the volatile compound 4,8,12-trimethyl-1,3,7,11-tridecatetraene (TMTT), which is released by many plants in response to damage.
